The paper proposes a method for detecting salient objects in videos using both spatial and temporal information. This involves combining static and dynamic features, analyzing saliency cues through a multiscale segmentation model, and using an adaptive temporal window. These techniques are all commonly used in computer vision and machine learning, suggesting that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and fusing data across multiple scales, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also involves developing an adaptive temporal window, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT).
